{"timestamp": "2026-05-06T23:55:49.183865", "level": "ERROR", "logger": "core.command_parser", "message": "Failed to parse LLM response as JSON: Invalid control character at: line 4 column 268 (char 318)\nResponse: {\n  \"intent\": \"write_text\",\n  \"target\": \"notepad\",\n  \"content\": \"Friendship is a bond that transcends time and space. It's the unwavering support system that helps us navigate life's ups and downs. A true friend is someone who accepts you for who you are, flaws and all, and still manages to bring out the best in you.\n\nIn today's fast-paced world, it's easy to get caught up in our own lives and forget about the people around us. But a good friend never lets that happen. They're always there to lend an ear, offer advice when needed, or simply be present. Whether we need someone to share a joke with, a shoulder to cry on, or a partner in crime for our wild adventures, friends are always there to provide.\n\nWhat makes friendship truly special is the deep emotional connection we form with others. It's the ability to be vulnerable and open, knowing that our secrets are safe and our feelings will be understood. Friends have the power to bring out the best version of us, helping us grow and evolve as individuals.\n\nIn addition to the emotional support they provide, friends also play a crucial role in shaping our sense of identity. They're the ones who introduce us to new experiences, help us discover hidden talents, and show us that we're capable of achieving great things. Without friends, we might be missing out on opportunities to explore our passions and pursue our dreams.\n\nAs we grow older, friendships may evolve, but their importance never fades. Whether it's a childhood pal, a college roommate, or a colleague at work, true friends are always there to offer support, encouragement, and love.\n\nIn conclusion, friendship is the glue that holds us together. It's the foundation upon which we build our lives, the source of our strength and resilience. So let's cherish these bonds, nurture them with care, and celebrate the joy they bring to our lives.\"\n}"}
